'''Kanbara Shrine''' (かんばらじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Nagamine-chō, Chūō Ward, Niigata City, Niigata Prefecture.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Kukunochi|Q10749920|qid=Q10749920|lt=Kukunochi-no-Mikoto|1=Kukunochi}}
* {{ill|lt=Haniyasu|Q9285919|qid=Q9285919|lt=Haniyamahime-no-Mikoto|1=Haniyasu-hiko and Haniyasu-hime}}
* {{ill|lt=Mizuhanome|Q8191796|qid=Q8191796|lt=Mizuhanome-no-Mikoto|1=Mizuhanome}}
* {{ill|lt=Kanayamahiko-no-Kami|Q4387856|qid=Q4387856|lt=Kanayamahiko-no-Mikoto|1=Kanayama-hiko and Kanayama-hime}}
* Homusukon-no-Mikoto
or
* {{ill|lt=Shiinezu-hiko|Q11120574|qid=Q11120574|lt=Shiinezu-hiko-no-Mikoto|1=Saonetsuhiko}}

=== Associated deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|qid=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu-Ōmikami|1=Amaterasu}}
* {{ill|lt=Yamato Takeru|Q461258|qid=Q461258|lt=Yamato Takeru-no-Mikoto|1=Yamato Takeru}}
* {{ill|qid=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata|Q9150391|qid=Q9150391|qid=Q9150391|lt=Takeminakata-no-Mikoto|1=Takeminakata}}
* {{ill|lt=Sugawara no Michizane|Q382005|qid=Q382005|1=Sugawara no Michizane}}
* {{ill|lt=Hatakeyama Shigetada|Q3128268|qid=Q3128268|1=Hatakeyama Shigetada}}
* {{ill|lt=Hatakeyama Shigemune|Q61055753|qid=Q61055753|1=Hatakeyama Shigemune}}

=== History ===
The original shrine was “Ōmi no Yashiro,” said to have stood on Kinbachi-yama, with Shiinezu-hiko as principal deity, alongside five-element deities (fire, water, wood, metal, earth), and others including Sugawara no Michizane.

Tradition says samurai {{ill|lt=Hatakeyama Shigemune|Q61055753|qid=Q61055753|1=Hatakeyama Shigemune}} of early Kamakura period is enshrined here, so it is also called “Rokurō-sama.”

In {{ill|lt=1688|Q7671|qid=Q7671|1=1688}} (Genroku 1), a breach of the {{ill|lt=Shinano River|Q734455|qid=Q734455|1=Shinano River}} led to relocation from Kinbachi-yama to current site.

In {{ill|lt=1968|Q2644|qid=Q2644|1=1968}} (Shōwa 43), because the colloquial name “Kanbara Festival” became famous, the shrine name was changed from “Gosha Shrine” to “Kanbara Shrine.”

=== Precincts ===
* Kotodama Keyaki

=== Main buildings ===
* Main sanctuary
* Kagura hall
* Shrine office

=== Cultural properties ===
* Two wooden seated Buddhist-style statues of Hatakeyama Shigemune and wife
** Designated Niigata Prefecture Tangible Cultural Property (sculpture) on March 24, 2009.

=== Annual events ===
* {{ill|lt=Kanbara Festival|Q11621265|qid=Q11621265|1=Kanbara Matsuri}}
* Oracle rite (otakusen)
* Plum festival
* Chrysanthemum festival

=== Local information ===
; Address
* Nagamine-chō 3-18, Chūō Ward, Niigata City, Niigata Prefecture

; Access
* Rail
** About 15 minutes on foot from {{ill|lt=Niigata Station|Q701753|qid=Q701753|1=Niigata Station}} (Bandai exit)
* Car
** About 20 minutes from Niigata-Nishi IC or Niigata-Chūō IC via Route 7 bypass

